</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,1290]" pageId="3" pageNumber="299">
In the treatment of species below, descriptions are given for those species not treated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Avalos-Hernandez, O." pageId="3" pageNumber="299" pagination="1 - 49" refId="ref13842" refString="Avalos-Hernandez, O. (2009) A review of the North American species of Hemipenthes Loew, 1869 (Diptera: Bombyliidae). Zootaxa, 2074 (1), 1 - 49. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2074.1.1" type="journal article" year="2009">Ávalos-Hernández (2009)</bibRefCitation>
and for new species. For descriptions of other Nearctic species and associated male genitalia descriptions and illustrations, the reader is directed to 
<bibRefCitation author="Avalos-Hernandez, O." box="[570,866,1193,1220]" pageId="3" pageNumber="299" pagination="1 - 49" refId="ref13842" refString="Avalos-Hernandez, O. (2009) A review of the North American species of Hemipenthes Loew, 1869 (Diptera: Bombyliidae). Zootaxa, 2074 (1), 1 - 49. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2074.1.1" type="journal article" year="2009">Ávalos-Hernandez (2009)</bibRefCitation>
. Illustrations of wings are presented for all species available for study and descriptions for female genitalia where numbers of specimens allowed dissection.
</paragraph>
